def: The state or quality of being indispensable, or absolutelynecessary. S. Clarke.
Of or pertaining to glosses or to a glossary; containing aglossary.
A Mexican spinous lizard (Phrynosoma orbiculare) having a headsomewhat like that of a toad; -- called also horned toad.
A version to food; refusal to take nourishment. [Written alsositiophobia.]
Exaction of forced service; compulsion. [Obs.] Speed.
An old game, played by holding up the fingers. Herrick.
Anything made so as to form alternate squares lke those of acheckerboard.
The period or state of full expansion in a flower. Gray.
To render Italian, or conformable to Italian customs; toItalianize. [R.] Ascham.
